ExpandRouteReplyPacket Class Reference

Packet sent as reply to the ExpandRouteRequestPacket, containing the route in the wanted format (string or graphical). More...

List of all members.

Add NAVIGATOR-data

Add data when the route type is ROUTE_TYPE_NAVIGATOR.

The information stored is the map id, item id, speedlimit, attributes (motorway flag) and all coordinates for that item. These methods must be called in the correct order.

First call the setNavItemData method, which will store the item and map id, as well as the speedlimit. Store the return value of this method and use that when adding the coordinates.

Then add the coordinates for that item by calling addCoordToItemData(lat, lon, nbrCoordPos) for each coordinate that should be added. The parameter nbrCoordPos should be set to the return value of setNavItemData().

  • uint32 setNavItemData (uint32 mapID, uint32 itemID, byte speedLimit, byte attributes)
    Add one data-item to this packet, with speedlimit and with all coordinates (added later by method addCoordToItemData).
  • void addCoordToNavItemData (int32 lat, int32 lon, uint32 nbrCoordPos)
    Adds one coordinate (can be called several times) to a data-item.

  • void extractAttributes (byte attributes, bool &freeway, bool &ramp, bool &driveOnRightSide)
    Static method to extract the additional attributes from the attribute bitfield (from the packet).

Detailed Description

Packet sent as reply to the ExpandRouteRequestPacket, containing the route in the wanted format (string or graphical).

After the normal ReplyPacket-header the ExpandRouteReplyPacket contains: Table begins at REPLY_HEADER_SIZE
PosSizeComment
0 1 bytes Route type
1 1 bytes Heading
2 2 bytes Start angle
2 2 bytes Number of strings in stringtable
4 4 bytes Size of the stringtable
8 2 bytes Number of items
10 2 bytes Number of nbr of items per string
12 4 bytes size of item data
16 4 bytes Total distance
20 4 bytes Total time
24 4 bytes Total standstill time
28 2 bytes Ordinal number of the reply
30 1 bytes Last segment's left street count
31 1 bytes Last segment's right street count
32 2 bytes Start offset
34 2 bytes End offset
36 1 bit U-turn
37 x bytes Latitude of destination
41 x bytes Longitude of destination
45 x bytes String data starts here

The format of string data follows:
PosSizeComment
0 4 bytes StringCode
4 4 bytes Distance
8 4 bytes Time
12 4 bytes Lat
16 4 bytes Lon
20 1 bytes transport
21 1 bytes nametype
22 1 byte turn number
23 1 byte crossing kind
24 Objects Lanes
x Objects SignPosts
x list Landmarks

uint32  stringCode,

LandmarkHead *  landmarks
) 
 

Add one stringdata to this packet.

Warning:
All strings must be added (by using this method) before you call the other methods that adds data, e.g. setItemData() / setNavItemData().
Parameters:
str The string.
stringCode The turndesc etc. to be displayed next to the string. NB! The most significant (leftmost) byte describes the exitcount.
transport The type of transoprtation (e.g walk, drive).
dist The dist to be displayed if 0 no dist will be displayed.
time The time to be displayed if 0 no time will be displayed.
lat The latitude of the turn. (Default 0).
lon The longitude of the turn.(Default 0).
nameType The type of the name ( Default 0 ).
